      <hedline>
        <hl1>City Traffic Solutions</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>City Traffic Solutions**Jeff Travia letter, commenting on August 4 article, says passenger rail or automobile traffic should be incorporated in plans for freight-train tunnel in New York Harbor</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Study Backs Freight-Train Tunnel in New York Harbor'' (news article, Aug. 4):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Study Backs Freight-Train Tunnel in New York Harbor'' (news article, Aug. 4):</p>
        <p>It is unfortunate that there are no plans to incorporate passenger rail or automobile traffic into the proposed tunnel. With worsening traffic tie-ups on the VerrazanoNarrows Bridge and in the Holland Tunnel, would it not make sense to provide an additional crossing?</p>
        <p>As employment and housing scatter about the region, New York and New Jersey desperately need alternatives to Manhattan-centric public transit. Perhaps, with a little engineering intuition, a rail line could link Newark directly with Brooklyn, Queens and Kennedy Airport.</p>
        <p>JEFF TRAVIA  Glen Mills, Pa., Aug. 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
